Question: Do you have any additional ideas, concerns, or feedback you would like to share to help ACME better serve the public?

Response ID: resp_3535
Response Text: Consistent grant deadlines: it's hard to plan for the future when you're not sure when, or if, a program is going to launch.  Major changes don't need to be made every 2 or 3 years unless something is glaringly wrong.  It takes time to see how a program will play out and major changes without analyzing the results can lead to unintended consequences, as well as confusion on when the grant will be ready again.  Tweaks or relatively easy to incorporate changes should be done for this round with major changes receiving the attention they deserve for a rollout in the next round.  The equity focus of the programs is great and I hope that won't go away since the DEI language bills failed to pass in the Texas Legislature and there are no federal restrictions affecting municipal funders.  Austin needs to continue being the beacon and example of taking equity seriously and doing it right.

